'''Nilson David Angulo Ramírez''' (born 19 June 2003) is an Ecuadorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[winger (association football)|winger]] or [[wide midfielder]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team.]]

==Club career==
Angulo started his senior career at [[L.D.U. Quito|LDU Quito]]. In June 2022, he joined [[Belgian First Division A]] side [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] on a five-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rsca.be/en/angulo |title=BIENVENIDO, NILSON ANGULO |publisher=[[R.S.C. Anderlecht]] |date=21 June 2022 |accessdate=22 June 2022}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club in a 2–1 away win over [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] on 5 February 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/674600/anderlecht-club-brugge |title=Club Brugge 1–2 Anderlecht |publisher=ESPN |date=5 February 2024 }}</ref>

===Sunderland===
On 2 February 2026, Angulo signed for [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] on a four-and-a-half year deal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.safc.com/news/2026/february/02/nilson-angulo-signs-for-sunderland/|title=Nilson Angulo Signs for Sunderland|publisher=[[Sunderland A.F.C.]]|date=2 February 2026|access-date=2 February 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
In October 2021, Angulo made his senior international debut for [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]], playing in a 3–2 friendly win over [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/10/28/world/friendlies/mexico/ecuador/3624760/ |title=MEXICO VS. ECUADOR  2 - 3 |website=soccerway.com |date=28 October 2021 |accessdate=22 June 2022}}</ref>

On 9 May 2023, Angulo was called up for the [[2023 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in Argentina.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ecuavisa.com/deportes/futbol-internacional/mundial-sub-20-estos-son-los-convocados-de-ecuador-que-disputaran-este-torneo-CG5091455|title=Mundial Sub 20: Estos son los convocados de Ecuador que disputaran este torneo|publisher=[[Ecuavisa]]|first=Fernando|last=Guevara|date=9 May 2023|language=es}}</ref>

